@party_selection

- @esquerra: Republican Left of Catalonia - <span style='color: #ff8000; font-weight: bold;'>ERC</span>
- @cup: Popular Unity Candidacy - <span style='color: #C4B156; font-weight: bold;'>CUP</span>
- @ciu: Convergence and Union - <span style='color: #002782; font-weight: bold;'>CiU</span>

@esquerra
title: Republican Left of Catalonia (ERC)
face-image: img/parties/logo_erc.svg

**Republican Left of Catalonia - <span style='color: #ff8000; font-weight: bold;'>ERC</span>**
The left-wing republican party advocates for Catalan independence, socialism, and anti-austerity measures. Formed in 1931, it endured Franco's dictatorship and re-emerged post-1975. It governed in as part of the 2003-2010 tripartite coalition with <span style="color: #e73b39; font-weight: bold;">PSC</span> and <span style="color: #67af2f; font-weight: bold;">ICV-EUiA</span> but lost support after compromising for governance, poor economic leadership, and the failed new charter of autonomy. Now in 2012 is seems to be the main beneficiary of the growing independence sentiment, pushing for a referendum on self-determination.

- @esquerra_2: Yes, we'll be the left of a new country!
- @party_selection: No, select a different party.


@esquerra_2
on-arrival: {!
Q.player_party = "erc";
Q.player_party_name = "<span style='color: #ff8000; font-weight: bold;'>ERC</span>";
Q.position_disp = "<span style='font-style: italic;'>opposition</span>"; 

Q.ciu_relations = 55;
